name: Wandering Stragglers
des: Easily manageable with an echelon trained to a reasonable level.
log_fitter_name: A group of regular enemies with negligible armor and moderate amount of health.

name: Concentrated Wraiths
des: Wraiths are composites of all horrors and ought to be wiped out in one go. (Echelons with good AoE damage recommended.)
log_fitter_name: A swarm of tightly-packed enemies with moderate to large amount of health.

name: Guns and Shields
des: Shields are rather bothersome, but without the pikes behind them, they become pointless. (Echelons that target the back row recommended.)

name: Twisted Faith
des: If you can't defeat enemies with strong faith, then destroy their faith first – starting with the force field. (Echelons capable of tearing down a single high-health target and effective against enemies with force fields recommended.)

name: Mobile Explosives
des: The best way to stop nightmares is to wake up at once...or just strangle it before it happens. (Echelons with high burst damage right off the bat recommended.)

name: Sturdy Iron Wall
des: If going straight at them proves difficult, try punching through that annoying armor! (Echelons capable of tearing down high-health targets and effective against enemies with force fields recommended. It might also be easier if your front row units are tanky.)

name: Storm of Destruction
des: It is unwise to engage multiple Manticores – unless you're very experienced or know their weaknesses.

name: Keen-Eyed Hunter
des: The abandoned Patrolers want to prove their worth by killing you. If you're still a rookie, avoid them.

name: Coeus!
des: Don't try to suppress it with any sort of tactics. This thing is the embodiment of tactical suppression.
